<section xml:id="MTH-4" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Desired Outcomes</title>  
    <introduction>
        Desired outcomes  
        <ul>
            <li>Students will view themselves and members of  their communities as mathematicians in the present, past, and future. </li>
            <li>Students will be able to use mathematics to comprehend, analyze, and  ask questions about their issues relevant to their own lives and their communities.</li>
            <li>Students will be able to identify issues of power and oppression in the ways mathematics is used and taught. </li>
            <li>Students will be able to identify and explore the roles  which mathematics can play in relation to their academic goal, personal well being, and the well being of their communities..  </li>
        </ul>
    </introduction>
</section>
